markets.title: Will the injunction on student loan forgiveness be lifted in Biden v. Nebraska?
markets.rules_primary: If, in Biden v. Nebraska, the Supreme Court vacates or otherwise lifts the injunction placed by the Eighth Circuit enjoining the United States Secretary of Education from implementing its plan to discharge student loan debt under the Higher Education Relief Opportunities for Students Act of 2003, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: A ruling that narrows the injunction to specific states, including the plaintiff states, would not be encompassed in the Payout Criterion. A ruling that otherwise prohibits the Secretary of Education’s plan to discharge student loan debt under the HEROES Act–either on statutory, constitutional, or other grounds–would likewise not be encompassed in the Payout Criterion. Any ruling on the Biden administration’s modification to income-driven repayment plans does not affect the Payout Criterion.
